          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 180 target was prepared in situ in the following",
                "way: A piece of Ti foil placed approximately 10 mm",
                "from a 10 mu-g/cm2 carbon foil was heated in an 180",
                "atmosphere of = 5 X 10-7 mbar until a pressure drop",
                "was observed. The decrease in pressure is due to the",
                "pumping effect (gettering) of the chemically active,",
                "freshly evaporated Ti film. After 15 min a suitable",
                " (non-stoichiometric) titanium-oxide layer was formed",
                "on the carbon backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two bakeable solid-state detectors were used",
                "to detect scattered particles and reaction products.",
                "One detector is fixed and detects particles at a",
                "lab. angle of 144 0. The other detector is movable and",
                "detects particles with scattering angles between 0 and",
                "130 degr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
